   <back>
      <fn-group xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
         <title>[Footnotes]</title>
         <fn id="d22e144a1310">
            <label>*</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d22e151" publication-type="other">
In the Budget Sir Geoffrey Howe, Chancellor of the Exchequer, did in fact incorporate the
proposals put forward by the previous Administration in August, 1978. The only modifications were
certain changes in the PRT expenditure rules. The modifications suggested in the conclusions of this
paper were not incorporated.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d22e167a1310">
            <label>*</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d22e174" publication-type="other">
The projections in Table 1 are based on Johnson (1979). They do not incorporate the results of the
oil price rises in 1979, which would make them somewhat higher. But as pointed out below, the
unexpected rise in the sterling/dollar exchange rate has reduced the sterling value of the North Sea oil
revenue.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d22e190a1310">
            <label>*</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d22e197" publication-type="other">
A similar point is made for the UK economy as a whole in Beenstock (1979).</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
